<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Channel 10 is rumoured to be planning a relaunch of Australian Idol.</p>

<p>After a swathe of classic shows were remade this year, including Farmer Wants a Wife and Big Brother, the network is said to be considering rebooting Idol with inaugural winner Guy Sebastian as its marquee judge.</p>

<p>'They're eager to get him involved - they know the show's success is dependent on a brilliant judging line-up,' an insider told Woman's Day. </p>

<p>Blast from the past: Rumours are swirling that Channel 10 is looking to bring back Australian Idol with inaugural winner Guy Sebastian (pictured in 2003) as a judge </p>

<p>'If all goes to plan, the show will be back with Guy,' the source added. 'Getting him back on the show that made him famous would be a dream.'</p>

<p>Seven reportedly had the opportunity to reboot the franchise in February, but did not make an announcement or release a casting call.</p>

<p>Guy is believed to be currently signed to Channel Nine.</p>

<p>Familiar face: Guy was most recently a judge on Nine's The Voice, but his position is said to be up in the air after Seven acquired rights to the program</p>

<p>He was most recently a judge on The Voice Australia, but his position is said to be up in the air after Seven acquired rights to the program.</p>

<p>The 38-year-old famously won Australian Idol's first season in 2003.</p>

<p>He went on to have a successful career as a solo artist and also represented his country at the 2015 Eurovision Song Contest, finishing in fifth place.</p>

<p>Accomplished: Guy, 38, famously won Australian Idol's first season in 2003. He went on to have a successful career and also represented his country at the 2015 Eurovision Song Contest</p>

<p>In addition, he has served as a judge on a variety of talent shows. </p>

<p>Daily Mail Australia has contacted Channel 10 and Guy Sebastian's manager for comment. </p>

<p>Australian Idol, based on the global Pop Idol format, aired from 2003 to 2009 on Channel 10. Former winners include Jessica Mauboy and Stan Walker. </p>

<p>Veteran: Guy has been a judge on several talent shows, including The Voice and The X Factor</p>
